---

<Layout
  title="Who Actually Gets Scammed in America? | Ranking Atlas"
  description="Federal fraud and survey data show sharp divides in who gets scammed, how often, and how much they lose."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />

<div class="bg-white">

  <!-- ── 1. Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="pt-20 md:pt-28 pb-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3 text-center">Data Report</div>
      <h1 class="font-serif font-medium text-[1.75rem] md:text-[2rem] lg:text-[2.25rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-[1.15] mb-3 text-center">
        Who Actually Gets Scammed in America?
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif italic text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[1.55] text-body mt-2 mb-8">
        Federal fraud and survey data show sharp divides in who gets scammed, how often, and how much they lose (and it's not who you think).
      </p>

      <figure class="mb-8">
        <img
          src="/assets/images/resources/generational-fraud/hero.jpg"
          alt="Illustrative composition representing generational fraud risk across age cohorts in the United States."
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </figure>

      <div class="bg-[#FBFAF7] border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 rounded-2xl p-5 mb-6">
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Content Written By:</p>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Daniel Grainger</p>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Founder, Ranking Atlas</p>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Published March 2026</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="bg-[#FBFAF7] border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 rounded-2xl p-5" aria-label="Article sections">
        <p class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Navigation</p>
        <ul class="flex flex-col space-y-2 text-[14px]">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#key-takeaways" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Key Takeaways</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#identity-theft-by-age" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Identity Theft Rate Peaks Among Americans Aged 50 to 64</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#frequency-vs-severity" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Adults Over Eighty Lose Four Times More Per Incident Than Adults in Their Twenties</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#social-media" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Social Media Converts Seven in Ten Fraud Attempts to a Financial Loss</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#index" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Weighing Frequency, Volume, and Severity Together Puts Ages 50 to 64 First</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#reporting-gap" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Only One in Twenty Identity Theft Victims Reports the Crime to Police</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#methodology" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Methodology</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#limitations" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Limitations</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Key Takeaways ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="key-takeaways" class="py-16 bg-[#FBFAF7] border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7]">
        <li><strong>Americans aged 50 to 64 record the highest identity theft rate in the country at 10.9% (BJS).</strong> They sit at the intersection of peak earnings, the most active credit lines, and the largest investable assets, yet remain online at roughly the same scale as younger cohorts. The group treated as low-risk in most public fraud messaging is in fact the most exposed.</li>
        <li><strong>Adults in their twenties get caught most often, but adults aged 80 and over lose roughly four times more per incident ($1,650 vs $417, FTC).</strong> Younger victims are picked off in volume by low-stake scams like fake jobs, delivery texts, and marketplace fraud. Older victims are picked off less often, but by attacks that exploit deeper trust: impersonated relatives, fraudulent investments, urgent transfer instructions from someone posing as a bank or family member. The result is fewer events, each one capable of clearing decades of savings.</li>
        <li><strong>Social media now extracts money from 70% of the victims it reaches, the highest conversion rate of any fraud channel (FTC).</strong> Email is the inverse: 25% of all fraud reports but only 11% convert to a loss. Inboxes have become noisy enough that targets ignore them, while social platforms still carry the implicit trust of a curated feed.</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile banking is now the primary account-access method for 48.3% of US households, up from 5.4% a decade ago (FDIC).</strong> The device that delivers most fraud now also handles most banking, so the contact, persuasion, and transfer can all take place on the same screen.</li>
        <li><strong>Only 6.6% of identity theft victims report the crime to police, and just 18% report to the FTC or FBI (BJS, AARP).</strong> Two-thirds resolve fraud privately through their bank, where the case is closed and never enters federal statistics. The FTC's own model places true 2023 losses between $23.7 billion and $158.3 billion, against the $10 billion officially recorded. Every published fraud figure is an undercount.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. Finding 1: BJS by age ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="identity-theft-by-age" class="py-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6 max-w-3xl">Identity Theft Rate Peaks Among Americans Aged 50 to 64</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mb-8">
        <p>The Bureau of Justice Statistics asks a clean question every few years through the National Crime Victimization Survey: in the past twelve months, did anyone misuse your personal information? The most recent published wave (2021) is the cleanest population-level estimate of identity theft prevalence in the United States. The survey covers 263 million Americans aged 16 or older.</p>
        <p>The result by age band:</p>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8 bg-[#FBFAF7]">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">Age group</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">BJS victimisation rate (12-month)</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">2024 US population</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">Implied affected population</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#0A0F1E]/6">
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">16–17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">1.4%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">9,070,885</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">~127,000</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">18–24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">7.0%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">31,363,181</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">~2.2 million</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">25–34</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">8.9%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">46,453,864</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">~4.1 million</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">35–49</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">9.9%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">65,833,273</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">~6.5 million</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-brand/5 hover:bg-brand/10 transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">50–64</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink font-semibold">10.9% (highest)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink">62,148,032</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink font-semibold">~6.8 million</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">65+</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">8.6%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">55,747,169</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">~4.8 million</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[#64748B] max-w-3xl">
        Source: <a href="https://bjs.ojp.gov/library/publications/victims-identity-theft-2021" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">BJS NCJ 306474</a>, Table 2 (2021 survey data). Population denominators: <a href="https://www.census.gov/data/tables/time-series/demo/popest/2020s-national-detail.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">US Census Bureau NC-EST2024-AGESEX-RES</a>. Implied affected population applies 2021 BJS rates to 2024 Census figures for directional illustration.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mt-8">
        <p>Roughly 1 in 9 Americans aged 50 to 64 experienced identity theft in a single twelve-month window. Adults over 65, despite being the primary target of fraud-awareness campaigns, recorded a lower victimisation rate than every working-age cohort above 35.</p>
        <p>The BJS data does not explain why the 50 to 64 cohort tops the chart. It shows the cohort with the most active credit accounts and the largest investable assets carries the highest fraud frequency.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 5. Finding 2: Frequency vs severity ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="frequency-vs-severity" class="py-16 bg-[#FBFAF7] border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6 max-w-3xl">Adults Over Eighty Lose Four Times More Per Incident Than Adults in Their Twenties</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mb-8">
        <p>If victimisation rate is the first dimension of fraud risk, financial loss is the second. The FTC Consumer Sentinel Network Data Book 2024 tracks both whether complainants reported losing money and how much they lost. The two metrics move in opposite directions across the age curve.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8 bg-[#FBFAF7]">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">Age group</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">% reporting a fraud loss</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">Median loss per incident</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">Total reported losses</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#0A0F1E]/6">
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">20–29</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">44%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$417</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$430M</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">30–39</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">35%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$450</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$810M</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">40–49</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">38%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$500</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$971M</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">50–59</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">40%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$520</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1.18B</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-brand/5 hover:bg-brand/10 transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">60–69</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink font-semibold">51%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink font-semibold">$691</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink">$1.01B</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">70–79</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">24%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1,000</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$887M</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-brand/5 hover:bg-brand/10 transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">80+</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink">21%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink font-semibold">$1,650</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-ink">$319M</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[#64748B] max-w-3xl">
        Source: <a href="https://www.ftc.gov/reports/consumer-sentinel-network-data-book-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">FTC Consumer Sentinel Network Data Book 2024</a>, p. 13.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mt-8">
        <p>Younger Americans are caught by fraud more often; older Americans are caught less often but lose more when they are. The 80+ group loses 4 times more per incident than the 20 to 29 group.</p>
        <p>Preventing fraud among younger adults reduces the number of incidents. Preventing fraud among older adults reduces catastrophic financial losses. Generic awareness campaigns treat them as one problem and solve neither.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 6. Finding 3: Social media ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="social-media" class="py-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6 max-w-3xl">Social Media Converts Seven in Ten Fraud Attempts to a Financial Loss</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mb-8">
        <p>The FTC also tracks how fraud reaches its victims. Among complaints where the contact method was identified, social media and websites or apps are now the two channels most likely to extract money from the target.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8 bg-[#FBFAF7]">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">Contact method</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">% of reports</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">% with dollar loss</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">Aggregate loss</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink text-right">Median loss</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#0A0F1E]/6">
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Social media</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">13%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">70%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1,858M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1,500</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Website or app</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">12%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">68%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$976M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$990</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Mail</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">3%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">62%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$470M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1,000</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Phone call</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">19%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">19%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$948M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1,000</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Text</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">16%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">12%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$1,072M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$633</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Email</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">25%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">11%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$502M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$600</td></tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-[#FBFAF7] transition-colors"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Online ad or pop-up</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">3%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">40%</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$246M</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-[#64748B]">$180</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[#64748B] max-w-3xl">
        Source: <a href="https://www.ftc.gov/reports/consumer-sentinel-network-data-book-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">FTC Consumer Sentinel Network Data Book 2024</a>, p. 12. Based on 1,509,002 reports with contact method identified out of 2,600,678 total fraud reports.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mt-8">
        <p>Email is the most common contact method (25% of reports) but the lowest conversion to actual loss (11%). The volume of email-based fraud still produces $502M in aggregate reported losses, while the per-attempt success rate is low.</p>
        <p>Social media inverts that. Only 13% of fraud reports identify social media as the contact method, but when fraud arrives via social media, 70% of complainants report a financial loss, by some distance the highest conversion rate of any channel.</p>
        <p>The same digital surface that delivers most fraud now also handles most banking. The <a href="https://www.fdic.gov/household-survey/2023-fdic-national-survey-unbanked-and-underbanked-households-report" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">FDIC's 2023 household survey</a> records 48.3% of US banked households using mobile banking as their primary account access method, up from 5.4% a decade earlier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 7. Finding 4: The Index ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="index" class="py-16 bg-[#FBFAF7] border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6 max-w-3xl">Weighing Frequency, Volume, and Severity Together Puts Ages 50 to 64 First</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mb-8">
        <p>The preceding sections present each source separately. The question no individual source answers is which age cohort faces the greatest overall fraud burden when victimisation, complaint volume, and loss severity are weighed together.</p>
        <p>The Generational Fraud Risk Index combines those three dimensions into a single composite score per age band. Three components feed the score:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
          <li><strong>Victimisation rate (40%):</strong> BJS identity theft prevalence.</li>
          <li><strong>Complaint volume (25%):</strong> FTC complaints per capita.</li>
          <li><strong>Financial severity (35%):</strong> likelihood and scale of financial loss.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each component is normalised 0 to 100 across the five cohorts using min-max scaling, then combined with the weights above.</p>
      </div>

